# Environment File Conventions

## Location

- Env files belong in the relevant package or service subfolder (e.g. `server/.env`, `client/.env`)
- Never place env files at the repository root unless there is no service subfolder
- Infer the correct file from context: if the task is API/backend work, use the server env; if it is frontend/mobile work, use the client env

## Updating Variables

- Always update the real `.env` file as well as `.env.example` and variations.
- `.env.example` should reflect every variable that `.env` contains, with placeholder or documented values
